whereas.text:
Whereas, on May 24, 1915, the Allied Powers of England, France, and Russia jointly issued a
			 statement explicitly charging for the first time ever another government
			 of committing	crimes against  humanity and civilization;

Whereas Senate Concurrent Resolution 12, 64th Congress, agreed to February 9, 1916, resolved that the President of the United States be respectfully asked to designate a day on which the citizens
			 of this country may give expression to their sympathy by contributing
			 funds now being raised for the relief of the Armenians, who at the time were enduring starvation, disease, and untold suffering;
